<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-09T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G/374: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-09T11:00:00-03:00">December 9, 1933—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 9—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>40. Department’s instructions page 81.<note n="17" xml:id="d77fn17"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_89">p.
                                        89</ref>, last paragraph, and <ref target="#pg_90">p.
                                        90</ref>, first paragraph.</note> Telegraph subsequent
                                changes or contemplated changes if any in Latin American truce <pb facs="0258" n="170" xml:id="pg_170"/> membership. Referring to
                                Treaty Information, July, pages 11–13, should Bolivia and Ecuador be
                                considered members?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>